    • Method Detail

      • parseLatLng

        public static ParseResult<LatLng> parseLatLng(String latitude,
                              String longitude)
        This parses string representations of latitude and longitude values. It tries its best to interpret the values and indicates any problems in its result as OccurrenceIssue. When the ParseResult.STATUS is FAIL the payload will be null and one or more issues should be set in ParseResult.getIssues(). Coordinate precision will be 5 decimals at most, any more precise values will be rounded.
        Parameters:
        latitude - The decimal latitude
        longitude - The decimal longitude
        Returns:
        The parse result
